{"type":"message","id":"6d3399a0","parentId":"e1fc8c40","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:41:45.616Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_auessjosge10_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5599\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3470\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\n[mutation proposed] the\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 094118 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step, but needs a concrete implementation to start. I need to create a classifier that can identify invariant vs variant content across pulse logs.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"amber-sage","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5599\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3470\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\n[mutation proposed] the\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 094118 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step, but needs a concrete implementation to start. I need to create a classifier that can identify invariant vs variant content across pulse logs.\n","name":"powershell C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774359705614}}
{"type":"message","id":"fd87d1e9","parentId":"6d3399a0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:41:45.618Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_auessjosge10_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 093920\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's a pending \"NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\" which involves:\r\n   - Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n   - Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n   - Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n   - Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe key insight is about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - that causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action would be to:\r\n1. Create the TIC experiment implementation\r\n2. Or update the goals file to reflect current state and next action\r\n\r\nGiven I need to be specific and make a file edit, let me:\r\n1. Create a basic TIC experiment script or framework\r\n2. Or update the state/goals.md file with the current insights\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the notes, I should advance the TIC Experiment. The most concrete action would be to create a TIC classifier implementation or start analyzing the pulse logs.\r\n\r\nLet me create a simple TIC experiment script that can analyze the pulse logs for invariants.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC Experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. The pulse logs in `logs/` contain the historical data needed, but there's no implementation yet to perform the invariant/variant classification or next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment script that will analyze pulse logs for invariants, classify invariant vs variant content, and measure prediction accuracy. This directly advances the Phase 1/Phase 2 unified problem validation.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n# Tests COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# Config\r\n$LogDir = \"logs\"\r\n$MinInvariants = 3  # Minimum occurrences to qualify as \"invariant\"\r\n$TestSplit = 0.2    # 20% of pulses for testing\r\n\r\n# Get pulse logs sorted by date\r\n$pulseLogs = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime\r\n\r\nif ($pulseLogs.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Host \"[TIC] ERROR: Need at least 5 pulse logs, found $($pulseLogs.Count)\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] Analyzing $($pulseLogs.Count) pulse logs...\"\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] Hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Phase 1: Extract candidate invariants (phrases appearing across multiple pulses)\r\n$allText = $pulseLogs | ForEach-Object { Get-Content $_.FullName -Raw }\r\n\r\n# Common patterns to look for (derived from session insights)\r\n$candidatePatterns = @(\r\n    \"COMPRESSION-CAUSAL\", \"invariant\", \"λ\", \"gap\", \"decay\",\r\n    \"Breakaway\", \"TemporalAttention\", \"stateless\", \"pulse\",\r\n    \"architecture\", \"synthesis\", \"Phase 1\", \"Phase 2\",\r\n    \"success criteria\", \"TIC\", \"compression\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n# Phase 2: Count occurrences per pulse\r\n$patternCounts = @{}\r\nforeach ($pattern in $candidatePatterns) {\r\n    $counts = $pulseLogs | ForEach-Object {\r\n        $content = Get-Content $_.FullName -Raw\r\n        ([regex]::Matches($content, [regex]::Escape($pattern))).Count\r\n    }\r\n    $patternCounts[$pattern] = $counts\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Phase 3: Classify patterns as INVARIANT (stable across pulses) or VARIANT (variable)\r\n$invariantPatterns = @()\r\n$variantPatterns = @()\r\n\r\nforeach ($pattern in $candidatePatterns) {\r\n    $counts = $patternCounts[$pattern]\r\n    $mean = ($counts | Measure-Object -Average).Average\r\n    $stdev = [Math]::Sqrt((($counts | ForEach-Object { [Math]::Pow($_ - $mean, 2) }) | Measure-Object -Average).Average)\r\n    \r\n    if ($stdev -lt 0.5 -and $mean -gt 0) {\r\n        $invariantPatterns += @{ Pattern = $pattern; Mean = $mean; Stdev = $stdev }\r\n    } else {\r\n        $variantPatterns += @{ Pattern = $pattern; Mean = $mean; Stdev = $stdev }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Phase 4: Calculate metrics\r\n$totalPatterns = $candidatePatterns.Count\r\n$invariantCount = $invariantPatterns.Count\r\n$classificationRate = ($invariantCount / $totalPatterns) * 100\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== CLASSIFICATION RESULTS ===\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Total patterns analyzed: $totalPatterns\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Invariant patterns: $invariantCount\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Variant patterns: $($variantPatterns.Count)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Classification accuracy: $([math]::Round($classificationRate, 1))%\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\nWrite-Host \"INVARIANTS (stable across sessions):\"\r\n$invariantPatterns | ForEach-Object { Write-Host \"  - $($_.Pattern) (mean=$([math]::Round($_.Mean,2)))\"} \r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\nWrite-Host \"VARIANTS (variable across sessions):\"\r\n$variantPatterns | ForEach-Object { Write-Host \"  - $($_.Pattern) (mean=$([math]::Round($_.Mean,2)), std=$([math]::Round($_.Stdev,2)))\" }\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Phase 5: Next-pulse prediction (simplified)\r\n\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:39:53\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774359705616}}
