{"type":"message","id":"49a5b201","parentId":"aabe40bc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:42:20.212Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The most recent pulse log in the session folder is `pulse_2026-03-24 094118.md` (09:41:45). The one I read (`pulse_2026-03-24 093920.md`) was created at 09:39:53. Let me read the most recent one.","thinkingSignature":"24ae478d9318ec93b0d35985650365dd3947e9f35155d7c0e7804cfc3871588c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qn91muyew9z0_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 094118.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4161,"output":122,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16420,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774359736075}}
{"type":"message","id":"df2ad77d","parentId":"49a5b201","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:42:20.218Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qn91muyew9z0_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 094118\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. The session is about Phase 1 of an architecture project called \"Breakaway\"\r\n2. There's a pending TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment that needs to be implemented\r\n3. The goal is to classify pulse logs as invariant vs variant and predict next pulse content\r\n4. Recent pulse log is at `logs/pulse_2026-03-24_093920.md`\r\n\r\nI need to take ONE concrete action that advances the goals. The most immediate next step is implementing the TIC classifier experiment on the pulse logs.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist:\r\n- `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md` - the new doc about the hypothesis\r\n- `state/goals.md` - the goals file\r\n\r\nThe next action should be to implement the TIC classifier. I should create a script or start the experiment on the pulse logs.\r\n\r\nSince this is a stateless discontinuous agent (each pulse is fresh reconstruction), I should focus on concrete file edits that advance the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nA good concrete first step would be to:\r\n1. Read the pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Create the TIC classifier implementation\r\n3. Start the experiment\r\n\r\nLet me create a script that implements the TIC classifier. This is a concrete file edit that advances the goal.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step, but needs a concrete implementation to start. I need to create a classifier that can identify invariant vs variant content across pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that will analyze pulse logs for invariant/variant classification and next-pulse prediction, then run it against existing logs.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n# Classifier for Phase 1 - COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = \"logs\"\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d+)\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_pulse_metadata(content):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract key fields from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    sections = {}\r\n    current_section = \"header\"\r\n    current_content = []\r\n    \r\n    for line in content.split(\"\\n\"):\r\n        if line.startswith(\"### \"):\r\n            if current_content:\r\n                sections[current_section] = \"\\n\".join(current_content)\r\n            current_section = line[4:].strip().lower()\r\n            current_content = []\r\n        else:\r\n            current_content.append(line)\r\n    \r\n    if current_content:\r\n        sections[current_section] = \"\\n\".join(current_content)\r\n    \r\n    return sections\r\n\r\ndef extract_invariants(sections):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract likely-invariant content (goals, structure, patterns).\"\"\"\r\n    invariants = []\r\n    \r\n    # Goals are typically invariant across pulses\r\n    if \"goals\" in sections:\r\n        invariants.append((\"goals\", sections[\"goals\"][:200]))\r\n    \r\n    # Pending actions are structural invariants\r\n    if \"pending\" in sections:\r\n        invariants.append((\"pending_structure\", sections[\"pending\"][:200]))\r\n    \r\n    return invariants\r\n\r\ndef extract_variants(sections):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract likely-variant content (observations, actions, timestamps).\"\"\"\r\n    variants = []\r\n    \r\n    if \"observation\" in sections:\r\n        variants.append((\"observation\", sections[\"observation\"]))\r\n    \r\n    if \"action\" in sections:\r\n        variants.append((\"action\", sections[\"action\"]))\r\n    \r\n    return variants\r\n\r\ndef classify_content(pulse_path):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify pulse content as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    with open(pulse_path, \"r\") as f:\r\n        content = f.read()\r\n    \r\n    sections = extract_pulse_metadata(content)\r\n    invariants = extract_invariants(sections)\r\n    variants = extract_variants(sections)\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        \"path\": pulse_path.name,\r\n        \"invariants\": invariants,\r\n        \"variants\": variants,\r\n        \"invariant_ratio\": len(invariants) / max(1, len(invariants) + len(variants))\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariant_features, current_pulse):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse content from invariant features.\"\"\"\r\n    predictions = []\r\n    \r\n    for feature_type, feature_content in invariant_features:\r\n        if feature_type == \"goals\":\r\n            predictions.append(f\"Goals persist: {feature_content[:50]}...\")\r\n        elif feature_type == \"pending_structure\":\r\n            predictions.append(f\"Pending items structure maintained\")\r\n    \r\n    return predictions\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Run TIC classifier on all pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    log_files = sorted(\r\n        [f for f in Path(LOGS_DIR).glob(\"pulse_*.md\")],\r\n        key=lambda x: x.name\r\n    )\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"TIC EXPERIMENT: Analyzing {len(log_files)} pulse logs\\n\")\r\n    \r\n    results = []\r\n    for log_file in log_files:\r\n        result = classify_content(log_file)\r\n        results.append(result)\r\n        print(f\"  {result['path']}: invariant_ratio={result['invariant_ratio']:.2f}\")\r\n    \r\n    # Calculate aggregate statistics\r\n    avg_invariant_ratio = sum(r['invariant_ratio'] for r in results) / len(results)\r\n    \r\n    # Test next-pulse prediction\r\n    correct_predictions = 0\r\n    for i in range(len(results) - 1):\r\n        current = results[i]\r\n        next_inv = results[i + 1]['invariants']\r\n        predictions = predict_next_pulse(current['invariants'], current\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:41:45\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774359740217}}
